Description: DNLJ_ECOLI - Also known as dnaL, lig, lop, pdeC. Experimental evidence at protein level: Swiss-Prot protein existence level 1. DNA ligase that catalyzes the formation of phosphodiester linkages between 5'-phosphoryl and 3'-hydroxyl groups in double- stranded DNA using NAD as a coenzyme and as the energy source for the reaction. It is essential for DNA replication and repair of damaged DNA. From Escherichia coli (strain K12).
β-lactamase; bla; confers resistance to ampicillin, carbenicillin, and related antibiotics
transcription terminator for bacteriophage T7 RNA polymerase
bidirectional E. coli tonB-P14 transcription terminator
LacZα fragment of β-galactosidase; lacZ fragment
